## 5️⃣ Production‑grade design suggestions (optional but worth considering)

| 💡 Idea | Why it adds value |
|--------|-------------------|
| **Configuration via JSON schema** – let users drop a `patches.json` file that the hot‑patcher reads at startup. | No recompilation when you add a new rule; you can hot‑reload the file without restarting the IDE. |
| **Pluggable detection back‑ends** – expose an abstract `class DetectionEngine { virtual HallucinationDetection run(const QString&)=0; }`. The hot‑patcher can hold a `std::unique_ptr<DetectionEngine>` that you swap for a TensorRT, a Python script, or a rule‑engine. | Future‑proof – you can upgrade the AI model without touching the C++ glue. |
| **Atomic snapshot of statistics** – implement `QJsonObject snapshotStatistics() const` that copies the atomics once and then returns the JSON; the UI can poll this at 1 Hz without any lock contention. | Smooth UI charts even under heavy traffic. |
| **Rate‑limited logging** – wrap the `qInfo()/qWarning()` calls in a tiny helper that emits at most N messages per second. | Prevents the IDE log from flooding the console during a burst of hallucinations. |
| **Unit‑test harness** – in a test binary instantiate `AgentHotPatcher`, feed it known strings, and assert the emitted signals. Use `QSignalSpy` to capture signals. | Guarantees that future changes don’t break the detection logic. |
| **Graceful shutdown flag** – a `bool m_shuttingDown` that, when true, makes `interceptModelOutput` return the original model output immediately. | Allows the IDE to stop the hot‑patcher quickly during a forced exit. |
| **Behaviour‑patch priority & cooldown** – add `int priority` and `QDateTime lastApplied` fields to `BehaviorPatch`. The `applyBehaviorPatches` loop can respect priority and avoid re‑applying the same patch too frequently. | Prevents “spam” when a patch’s condition matches many lines in a large response. |

These are not required for a working prototype, but they will save you a lot of refactoring once you move from “demo” to “enterprise”.

